<TABLE BORDER=0 cellpadding=4 border=0 cellspacing=1 WIDTH="95%"><TR bgcolor="#000000"><TD COLSPAN=2><CENTER><FONT SIZE="2" COLOR="#00ff00" FACE="Verdana, Arial">T O P I C  &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; R E V I E W</font></CENTER></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#1f1f1f"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">wakoJOB</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">how is it that people get like 50k plat in 2 hours....such as when people take mass orders from people on ebay for money...i mean it can be possible to get that by killing monsters and shaz could it?<BR>if anyone knowz how they do it or what they are doing plz make a post or email me at oarko@hotmail.com</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#1f1f1f"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Paradigm</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Heres the steps:<P>1. Go to sebilis<BR>2. Win a fungi tunic<BR>3. Sell in East commons<BR>4. Enjoy your 50,000+ plat</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#1f1f1f"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">DarkPath</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Friend of mine camped the AC in SRo 24/7 for over 2 months. (He had SEQ set up to wake him at night.) He made upwards of 500k. Not worth it if you ask me. Boring.<P></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#1f1f1f"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Rahvin</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Idol of pharmed in droga, 20k a pop</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#1f1f1f"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">D23</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">What they are telling you, is basically, it doesn't happen. No one :makes" 50k plat in 2 hours. You might get seriously lucky and get a rare spawn, but the odds are that is why it is called a rare spawn. It doesn't happen often.<P>The way people get a ton of plat is to start out with a ton of plat or to have many people working to get items and sell them for plat.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#1f1f1f"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Sparr</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">gornit, a level 24 cyclops, drops upwards of 250pp per hour.  thats where i go for money when im really bored.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#1f1f1f"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Mikeb4kool</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Good money at high levels is just to farm HG's or seafuries...with HG's I just as a fire pet...it tears right thru them. (not praising post 50 fire pets mind you). But none the less good money at high levels.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#1f1f1f"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Robotic</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">First of all Gornit isn't level 24, he spawns between level 33 and 37.  Second of all he's not a Cyclops, he's a Hill Giant.  Thirdly he doesn't typically drop "upwards of 250pp per hour".  He drops as much as 45pp (from my personal experience)each spawn and spawns every 6 minutes.  However, 35+pp drops are fairly rare.  His "good" plat drops are typically in the mid 20's and he tends to go in streaks.  So you may get several 20+pp drops in a row or several 4pp drops in a row.<P>While it is entirely possible for him to drop 250pp in an hour it is more typical for him to drop  around 100pp per hour or a little less.  <P>I don't mind seeing posts about certain mobs, but I do think it's important to be as accurate as possible.  I'd hate to see some level 25 try to go solo him and get waxed for their efforts.  Gornit is tough to solo even at 40 as he tends to resist frequently.  He is a great place to make money non-the-less.<P><BR>Robotic</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#1f1f1f"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">JuiCe</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Hill Giants in Rathe Mountains are, from what I can tell, the best way to make money at lower levels.  Even when grouped you make out very nicely.  If that doesn't work for you, you could always try going to Frontier Mountains and killing Mountain Giants and selling their Legchoppers and what not.  Good luck selling the Weighted Axe.. (PoS).  If you're lucky, you'll get a Forest Loop.. which when I last sold one.. was worth 1k.  That's about the easiest ways I can figure.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#1f1f1f"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">SNEAKY</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">DarkPath,<BR>   If what you say is true ( and I do not believe it) your friend is a moronic idiot and needs to die. Don't you think that people would get suspicious if the same person killed the AC in SRO everytime it popped for 2 months? What a fucking moron.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#1f1f1f"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">DarkPath</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Sneaky,<BR>  My friend is a Ranger. And he wasnt the _only_ one that killed the cyclops. He usually got it about half the time. Go hang in SRO for a while and you will probably see several people doing the same thing SEQ or no SEQ. The AC is easy to see across most of the zone so even tracking isnt needed for the most part.<P>  I sort of agree with the moron part tho. Anyone who spends as much time as he did is probably a moron.<P>  BTW he didnt ebay any of the money. He just used it to buy high end items. <P> <P></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#1f1f1f"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Siege</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">If you think about it, I dont know if there is a single server where when the AC pops someone isnt all over it. The only thing SEQ will do is wake you up to see someone else kill it a majority of the time.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#1f1f1f"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">guice</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">not exactly. Servers are always slow at night, and early in the morning ( US times ), you can actually catch the AC w/nobody else in the zone.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#1f1f1f"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">EzSteve</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">ShowEQ certainly notified me in plenty of time to be the first person to the AC in SRo.<BR>In fact, I got it down to about 60% before the dogpile started.  By then, I was too far ahead for even wizzies to KS it.<P>I was watching TV at the time, when my alert went off.</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>
